1
00:00:03,462 --> 00:00:06,047
TRIP: CHIEF ENGINEER'S LOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

2
00:00:06,089 --> 00:00:07,591
THIS TURNED OUT TO BE
THE PERFECT SPOT

3
00:00:07,633 --> 00:00:09,718
TO TEST THE AUTOPILOT UPGRADES.

4
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:12,095
[ SIGHS ]

5
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:15,432
THE GAS GIANT HAS
DOZENS OF MOONS.

6
00:00:15,474 --> 00:00:21,229
IT'S LIKE A...
GRAVITATIONAL JIGSAW PUZZLE.

7
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:23,190
WATCH OUT, TRAVIS.

8
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:25,651
THESE MODIFICATIONS
ARE WORKING SO WELL,

9
00:00:25,693 --> 00:00:28,111
PRETTY SOON
WE WON'T NEED PILOTS ANYMORE.

10
00:00:28,153 --> 00:00:30,865
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
Archer: Archer to<i> Shuttlepod 1.</i>

11
00:00:30,906 --> 00:00:32,658
CAPTAIN?

12
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:35,577
Archer: Looks like you're about
to have some company, Trip.

13
00:00:35,619 --> 00:00:37,579
Sensors are picking up
a small...

14
00:00:37,621 --> 00:00:38,831
[ STATIC ]

15
00:00:38,873 --> 00:00:40,165
SAY AGAIN, CAPTAIN.

16
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:42,334
I'M PICKING UP
A LOT OF INTERFERENCE.

17
00:00:42,376 --> 00:00:44,586
Archer: There's a small vessel
approaching your position...

18
00:00:44,628 --> 00:00:46,755
[ BEEPING ]

19
00:00:54,889 --> 00:00:56,807
THIS IS COMMANDER
CHARLES TUCKER.

20
00:00:56,849 --> 00:00:59,351
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

21
00:01:09,987 --> 00:01:11,572
TUCKER TO<i> ENTERPRISE!</i>

22
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:12,907
MAYDAY!

23
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:14,867
I'M LOSING POWER. MAYDAY!

24
00:01:14,909 --> 00:01:18,954
IF YOU CAN HEAR ME,
I'M MAKING AN EMERGENCY LANDING,

25
00:01:18,996 --> 00:01:20,581
THRUSTERS ONLY.

26
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:22,165
I TAKE IT BACK, TRAVIS.

27
00:01:22,207 --> 00:01:25,377
I COULD USE A FLESH-AND-BLOOD
PILOT RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

28
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:36,263
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

29
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:39,516
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

30
00:01:39,558 --> 00:01:43,353
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

31
00:01:43,395 --> 00:01:46,815
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

32
00:01:46,857 --> 00:01:51,486
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

33
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:55,156
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

34
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:59,160
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

35
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:01,997
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

36
00:02:02,039 --> 00:02:05,292
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

37
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,461
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

38
00:02:07,502 --> 00:02:10,547
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

39
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:15,343
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

40
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,805
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

41
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:22,684
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

42
00:02:22,726 --> 00:02:25,437
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

43
00:02:25,479 --> 00:02:31,902
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

44
00:02:31,944 --> 00:02:33,445
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

45
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:35,447
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

46
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:39,576
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

47
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:43,831
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

48
00:03:00,305 --> 00:03:03,100
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> TO<i> SHUTTLEPOD 1.</i>

49
00:03:03,142 --> 00:03:06,227
COMMANDER TUCKER,
DO YOU READ ME?

50
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:09,606
MALCOLM?

51
00:03:09,648 --> 00:03:11,358
REED: I DETECTED WEAPONS FIRE,

52
00:03:11,399 --> 00:03:14,193
AND THEN BOTH SHIPS...
JUST DISAPPEARED.

53
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:15,863
LAST KNOWN POSITION?

54
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:21,284
APPROXIMATELY 50,000 KILOMETERS,
BEARING 003...

55
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,495
MARK 27, I THINK.

56
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:25,164
REED: I CAN'T BE MORE SPECIFIC.

57
00:03:25,204 --> 00:03:26,540
IT'S THE DAMNED INTERFERENCE.

58
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:28,709
T'POL: MANY OF THESE MOONS
HAVE ATMOSPHERES

59
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,752
THAT CONTAIN SELENIUM ISOTOPES.

60
00:03:30,794 --> 00:03:33,380
THAT'S MOST LIKELY WHAT'S
AFFECTING OUR SENSORS.

61
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:35,340
ARCHER: TRIP'S A GOOD PILOT.

62
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:37,092
IF HE WAS NEAR
ONE OF THOSE MOONS,

63
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:39,053
HE MOST LIKELY SET DOWN ON IT.

64
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,220
HOW MANY ARE THERE?

65
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:42,263
62.

66
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:45,851
THEN WE'D BETTER START LOOKING.

67
00:03:45,893 --> 00:03:47,102
TRAVIS.

68
00:03:47,144 --> 00:03:48,353
AYE, SIR.

69
00:03:48,395 --> 00:03:49,938
WE'LL SCAN EVERY MOON

70
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:52,232
EVEN IF WE HAVE TO DO IT
WITH BINOCULARS.

71
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:53,859
KEEP HAILING HIM.

72
00:04:21,511 --> 00:04:23,013
[ SIGHS ]

73
00:04:26,558 --> 00:04:29,436
TRIP: CHIEF ENGINEER'S LOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

74
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:31,772
FOR THE RECORD...

75
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:35,358
I WAS ATTACKED BY A SMALL CRAFT.

76
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:38,153
[ GROANS SOFTLY ]

77
00:04:38,195 --> 00:04:40,697
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I DID
TO PROVOKE THEM.

78
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:42,699
THEN SOMETHING
IN THIS MOON'S ATMOSPHERE

79
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:44,118
NEUTRALIZED MY ENGINES.

80
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:47,287
I WAS FORCED TO MAKE
AN EMERGENCY LANDING.

81
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:48,997
[ SIGHS ]

82
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:53,418
LOOKS LIKE I TOOK SOME DAMAGE
ON IMPACT.

83
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:56,713
MAIN POWER'S STILL OFF-LINE.

84
00:04:58,215 --> 00:05:02,719
I DON'T THINK
I'LL BE FLYING OUT OF HERE.

85
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:05,513
FIRST THINGS FIRST.

86
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:08,892
I'LL TRY AND GET
THE TRANSCEIVER WORKING...

87
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:15,899
CONTACT<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

88
00:05:26,243 --> 00:05:28,245
DAMN IT.

89
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:40,339
[ RUSTLING ]

90
00:05:47,222 --> 00:05:49,348
[ RUSTLING ]

91
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:27,846
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

92
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,359
[ PANTING ]

93
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:53,496
SON OF A BITCH
STOLE MY TRANSCEIVER.

94
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:01,629
ARCHER: WHO ARE THEY?

95
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,257
T'POL: AN ARKONIAN
MILITARY VESSEL.

96
00:07:03,298 --> 00:07:04,591
ARCHER: YOU'VE DEALT WITH THEM?

97
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:07,386
NO, BUT I'M AWARE
OF THEIR REPUTATION.

98
00:07:07,426 --> 00:07:08,970
IF WE'RE IN THEIR TERRITORY,

99
00:07:09,012 --> 00:07:10,931
WE SHOULD PROCEED
WITH EXTREME CAUTION.

100
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:13,016
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
HOSHI: THEY'RE HAILING US.

101
00:07:17,645 --> 00:07:20,523
ALIEN:<i> YOU ARE ON</i>
<i>AN UNAUTHORIZED COURSE.</i>

102
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:23,318
<i>LEAVE IMMEDIATELY.</i>

103
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,361
ARCHER: AND YOU ARE?

104
00:07:24,403 --> 00:07:25,904
<i>CAPTAIN KHATA'N ZSHAAR.</i>

105
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:28,531
<i>I HAVE ORDERS</i>
<i>TO DESTROY ANY VESSEL</i>

106
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:30,325
<i>THAT VIOLATES OUR TERRITORY.</i>

107
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:34,204
I'M CAPTAIN JONATHAN ARCHER
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

108
00:07:34,246 --> 00:07:37,498
WE WEREN'T AWARE THAT THIS
SYSTEM WAS CLAIMED BY ANYONE.

109
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:40,794
<i>WHY IS THERE A VULCAN</i>
<i>ON YOUR BRIDGE?</i>

110
00:07:42,963 --> 00:07:46,007
SUBCOMMANDER T'POL
IS MY SCIENCE OFFICER.

111
00:07:46,049 --> 00:07:50,470
<i>TURN YOUR SHIP AROUND.</i>

112
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:55,309
A MEMBER OF MY CREW IS MISSING.

113
00:07:55,350 --> 00:08:00,647
WE BELIEVE HE EXCHANGED WEAPONS
FIRE WITH A SMALL VESSEL.

114
00:08:00,688 --> 00:08:02,774
WAS IT ONE OF YOURS?

115
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:08,488
<i>WE SENT A PATROL SHIP</i>
<i>TO INTERCEPT YOUR SHUTTLE.</i>

116
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:10,991
<i>WE HAVE ALSO LOST CONTACT.</i>

117
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:15,495
THEN MAYBE WE CAN LOOK
FOR THEM TOGETHER.

118
00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:18,081
ONCE WE'VE RECOVERED
OUR CREWMAN,

119
00:08:18,123 --> 00:08:20,041
WE'LL BE MORE THAN HAPPY
TO LEAVE.

120
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:25,046
<i>IF YOUR SHUTTLE DID ENCOUNTER</i>
<i>MY PATROL SHIP,</i>

121
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:29,217
<i>YOUR CREWMAN IS ALREADY DEAD.</i>

122
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,052
ARCHER: EITHER WAY,

123
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:33,680
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE
UNTIL WE KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

124
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:38,518
NOW, IT SEEMS TO ME
WE HAVE A SIMILAR PROBLEM.

125
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,896
TWO MISSING PEOPLE AND 62 MOONS.

126
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:44,274
IT'LL GO A LOT FASTER

127
00:08:44,316 --> 00:08:47,527
IF WE USE BOTH OUR SHIPS
TO COORDINATE THE SEARCH.

128
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:50,613
THE SOONER WE GET STARTED,

129
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:53,908
THE SOONER WE'LL BE OUT
OF YOUR TERRITORY.

130
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:01,309
IT'S HIM.

131
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:03,895
I RECOGNIZE HIS SHUTTLECRAFT.

132
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:06,606
AND HE SEEMS ABOUT AS BAD OFF
AS I AM.

133
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:10,485
WHATEVER KNOCKED OUT MY ENGINES
PROBABLY DID THE SAME TO HIS.

134
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:12,028
[ SIGHS ]

135
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:13,572
IF I'D BROUGHT
A UNIVERSAL TRANSLATOR ALONG,

136
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,532
I'D BE ABLE TO EXPLAIN
TO THIS GUY

137
00:10:15,574 --> 00:10:18,910
THAT I'M JUST TRYING
TO GET OUT OF HERE LIKE HE IS.

138
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:23,248
ONE PIECE OF GOOD NEWS.

139
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,459
IT'S STARTING TO WARM UP
A LITTLE.

140
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,710
DAWN IS COMING.

141
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,555
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

142
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:45,728
[ GROANS ]

143
00:10:51,526 --> 00:10:53,361
TRIP, ON RECORDING:<i> </i>
<i>I'M COMING OUT NOW.</i>

144
00:10:53,403 --> 00:10:57,740
<i>I KNOW YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND ME.</i>

145
00:10:57,782 --> 00:11:00,118
<i>PLEASE DON'T FIRE.</i>

146
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:03,079
<i>I WANT TO TALK.</i>

147
00:11:03,121 --> 00:11:04,581
<i>I'M NOT ARMED.</i>

148
00:11:04,623 --> 00:11:05,957
<i>I WON'T HURT YOU.</i>

149
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:07,292
<i>WE NEED TO TALK.</i>

150
00:11:07,334 --> 00:11:10,753
<i>YOU HAVE SOMETHING</i>
<i>THAT BELONGS TO ME.</i>

151
00:11:12,506 --> 00:11:14,174
<i>I WANT IT BACK.</i>

152
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:16,551
<i>IF YOU UNDERSTAND ANYTHING</i>
<i>THAT I'M SAYING TO YOU,</i>

153
00:11:16,593 --> 00:11:21,097
<i>I WANT YOU TO LISTEN</i>
<i>VERY, VERY CLOSELY.</i>

154
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:24,643
<i>MARY HAD A LITTLE LAMB.</i>

155
00:11:24,683 --> 00:11:27,562
<i>ITS FLEECE AS WHITE AS SNOW.</i>

156
00:11:27,604 --> 00:11:33,067
<i>AND EVERYWHERE THAT MARY WENT,</i>
<i>THE LAMB WAS SURE TO GO.</i>

157
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:36,488
[<i> SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY</i> ]

158
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:44,078
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

159
00:12:15,193 --> 00:12:17,945
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

160
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:26,745
NOW...MAYBE WE CAN
INTRODUCE OURSELVES.

161
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:30,749
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

162
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:32,711
NICE TO MEET YOU, TOO.

163
00:12:32,751 --> 00:12:35,129
NOW, I DON'T WANT TO HURT YOU.

164
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,549
I JUST WANT MY TRANSCEIVER BACK.

165
00:12:38,675 --> 00:12:40,301
[ GRUNTS ]

166
00:12:41,553 --> 00:12:43,513
[ GROANS ]

167
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:56,109
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

168
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:11,790
I'M NO GOOD UNTIL
I'VE HAD MY COFFEE.

169
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:13,918
[ GROANING ]

170
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,878
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

171
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:20,799
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE
A UNIVERSAL TRANSLATOR ON YOU?

172
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:22,677
[ SHOUTING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

173
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:25,597
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
A WORD YOU'RE SAYING!

174
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:30,769
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

175
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:32,687
I CAN'T MAKE IT WORK!

176
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:34,731
IT'S BROKEN.

177
00:13:34,773 --> 00:13:36,775
YOU KNOW, "BROKEN."

178
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:40,027
I WAS TRYING TO MAKE REPAIRS
WHEN YOU STOLE IT.

179
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,238
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

180
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:45,700
WHAT?

181
00:13:45,742 --> 00:13:48,077
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

182
00:13:51,623 --> 00:13:55,335
YOU WANT ME TO FIX
YOUR TRANSCEIVER.

183
00:13:56,753 --> 00:13:58,129
IS THAT A YES OR A NO?

184
00:13:58,171 --> 00:13:59,380
KUSH'KA!

185
00:13:59,422 --> 00:14:01,174
KUSH'KA TO YOU, TOO!

186
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:06,805
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

187
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:12,393
YOU KILL ME,
AND I CAN'T FIX ANYTHING.

188
00:14:14,521 --> 00:14:17,273
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO
UNTIE ME.

189
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:19,317
I NEED MY HANDS.

190
00:14:19,359 --> 00:14:21,944
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

191
00:14:28,034 --> 00:14:32,372
I TRY ANYTHING,
I'M A DEAD MAN.

192
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:33,832
I GET THE MESSAGE.

193
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:49,055
ANY PROGRESS?

194
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:51,140
T'POL: WE'VE SEARCHED FIVE
OF THE MOONS.

195
00:14:51,182 --> 00:14:54,894
NO SIGN OF COMMANDER TUCKER
OR THE ARKONIAN SHIP.

196
00:14:54,935 --> 00:14:56,813
AND THE ARKONIANS?

197
00:14:56,855 --> 00:14:59,691
IT APPEARS THEY'VE MADE
NO PROGRESS, EITHER.

198
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:02,485
THEY'RE CONTINUING TO SEARCH
THE MOONS THEY AGREED TO.

199
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:04,445
THIS IS THEIR TERRITORY.

200
00:15:04,487 --> 00:15:06,656
THEY COULD HAVE CALLED
FOR MORE SHIPS TO HELP SEARCH.

201
00:15:06,698 --> 00:15:09,075
T'POL: I'M AFRAID THEY DON'T
TRUST US...

202
00:15:09,116 --> 00:15:11,285
PRIMARILY BECAUSE I'M A VULCAN.

203
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:13,246
WHAT'S THE BAD BLOOD?

204
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:16,374
WE MADE FIRST CONTACT
NEARLY A HUNDRED YEARS AGO,

205
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:19,293
NOT LONG AFTER THE ARKONIANS
DEVELOPED WARP DRIVE.

206
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:22,088
BUT FROM THE BEGINNING,
OUR RELATIONS WERE DIFFICULT.

207
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:24,340
YOUR PEOPLE
ACCEPTED VULCAN GUIDANCE...

208
00:15:24,382 --> 00:15:27,552
OPEN TO DIPLOMATIC
AND CULTURAL EXCHANGES.

209
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:30,430
THE ARKONIANS
WERE SUSPICIOUS AND DECEITFUL.

210
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:34,434
EVENTUALLY, THE HIGH COMMAND
WITHDREW ITS CONTINGENT.

211
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:38,897
WELL...MAYBE WE'LL HAVE
BETTER LUCK WITH THEM.

212
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,106
IT DOESN'T APPEAR PROMISING.

213
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:41,941
THEY AGREED TO WORK WITH US.

214
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:43,693
FOR NOW.

215
00:15:43,735 --> 00:15:45,986
I'D ADVISE YOU
TO REMAIN CAUTIOUS.

216
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,907
ARKONIANS ARE UNPREDICTABLE.

217
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,867
THEY'RE PRONE TO HOSTILITY.

218
00:15:50,909 --> 00:15:52,744
I'LL KEEP THAT IN MIND.

219
00:15:52,786 --> 00:15:56,372
LET ME KNOW WHEN WE REACH
THE NEXT MOON.

220
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:15,975
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

221
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:17,727
DAMN IT!

222
00:16:19,896 --> 00:16:21,940
ALIEN: DAMN IT!

223
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:27,779
WELL, LOOKS LIKE
WE'VE MADE SOME HEADWAY

224
00:16:27,821 --> 00:16:32,867
IN OUR FIRST CONTACT
BETWEEN HUMANS AND, UM...

225
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:35,244
WHATEVER YOU ARE.

226
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:36,830
UNFORTUNATELY, YOUR FIRST WORD

227
00:16:36,871 --> 00:16:41,000
IS SOMETHING YOU WOULDN'T
WANT TO USE IN POLITE COMPANY.

228
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:43,002
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

229
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:47,256
DAMN IT.

230
00:16:48,883 --> 00:16:52,595
NO. I'M TRIP.

231
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:55,139
TRIP.

232
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:57,851
ALIEN: TRIP.

233
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:01,187
ZHO'KAAN.

234
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:04,231
TRIP: ZHO'KAAN.

235
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:06,818
GREAT.

236
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:12,281
NOW THAT WE'VE BEEN
PROPERLY INTRODUCED...

237
00:17:12,323 --> 00:17:14,450
HOW ABOUT SOME WATER, ZHO'KAAN?

238
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:17,578
IT'S GETTING...KIND OF HOT.

239
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:19,288
THIRSTY.

240
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:23,751
YOU KNOW...DRINK...WATER.

241
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:29,298
TRIP!

242
00:17:32,969 --> 00:17:34,888
THANKS.

243
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,063
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

244
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,774
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

245
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:01,706
SORRY.

246
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:12,383
I HAVE WATER IN MY SHUTTLE.

247
00:18:13,885 --> 00:18:15,428
WATER!

248
00:18:15,469 --> 00:18:18,138
SOMETHING I CAN DRINK.

249
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:24,062
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

250
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:25,605
TRIP.

251
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,455
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

252
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:05,728
THERE'S A MEDKIT
IN MY SHUTTLEPOD.

253
00:19:07,438 --> 00:19:10,357
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?
ARE YOU CRAZY?

254
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:24,622
THAT WAS QUITE A TRICK.

255
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:33,131
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

256
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,594
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

257
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:45,143
I CAN'T FIX THIS THING.

258
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,728
IT'S A LOST CAUSE.

259
00:19:47,770 --> 00:19:50,690
MAYBE IF YOU VOMIT ON IT,
IT'LL FIX ITSELF.

260
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,443
COME OVER HERE.

261
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:56,863
I WANT YOU TO SEE THIS.

262
00:19:58,238 --> 00:19:59,532
HERE.

263
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:03,243
COME HERE.

264
00:20:06,664 --> 00:20:09,083
IT'S LIKE TALKING TO PORTHOS.

265
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:10,877
SEE THIS?

266
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:15,882
I TRIED BYPASSING THE INDUCTION
COIL, BUT IT DIDN'T WORK.

267
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:17,925
SEE?

268
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:19,343
IN HERE.

269
00:20:19,385 --> 00:20:21,054
[ GROANING ]

270
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:27,601
I CAN'T FIX THIS.

271
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:31,105
I NEED TO GET BACK TO MY SHIP.

272
00:20:31,147 --> 00:20:34,108
MY SHIP.

273
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,442
NOW, PICK 'EM UP.

274
00:20:36,777 --> 00:20:38,445
PICK THEM UP!

275
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:46,245
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

276
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:47,788
AH, SAME TO YOU.

277
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:50,208
NOW, LET'S GET GOING.

278
00:20:56,089 --> 00:20:58,257
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

279
00:20:58,298 --> 00:20:59,717
SEE FOR YOURSELF.

280
00:21:02,095 --> 00:21:04,180
ARCHER: I'LL NEED
A LITTLE HELP HERE.

281
00:21:04,222 --> 00:21:06,224
IT'S A THERMOKINETIC
ANALYSIS OF THE MOONS.

282
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:09,227
EACH OF THEM UNDERGOES
EXTREME TEMPERATURE VARIATIONS

283
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:10,770
DURING THEIR ORBITS.

284
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:12,312
ARCHER: GO ON.

285
00:21:12,354 --> 00:21:16,358
AT NIGHT, IT CAN DROP TO 5
OR EVEN 10 DEGREES BELOW ZERO.

286
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,693
ARCHER: DOESN'T SOUND SO BAD.

287
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:19,528
DURING THE DAY,
THE TEMPERATURE CAN RISE

288
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:23,365
TO AS HIGH AS 170 DEGREES.

289
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:28,121
WE BETTER HOPE THAT TRIP
LANDED ON THE NIGHT SIDE.

290
00:21:28,162 --> 00:21:31,373
AND THAT WE FIND HIM
BEFORE THE SUN RISES.

291
00:21:37,797 --> 00:21:40,133
DON'T GIVE ME THAT LOOK.

292
00:21:40,174 --> 00:21:42,551
YOU STARTED THIS.

293
00:22:08,368 --> 00:22:10,704
YOU WANT SOME FOOD?

294
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,175
FOOD.

295
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:33,519
[ HACKING ]

296
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:36,354
NOHKTO.

297
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:39,025
TRIP: NOHKTO.

298
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,945
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.

299
00:22:42,987 --> 00:22:46,490
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

300
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:49,910
V'DHOZE.

301
00:22:52,955 --> 00:22:57,293
YOU WANT FOOD FROM YOUR SHIP?

302
00:22:58,836 --> 00:23:02,506
V'DHOZE?
THAT MEANS FOOD?

303
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:05,134
V'DHOZE.

304
00:23:08,262 --> 00:23:11,307
V'DHOZE...

305
00:23:11,349 --> 00:23:12,516
SHIP.

306
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:15,477
ZHO'KAAN: SHIP.

307
00:23:19,357 --> 00:23:20,524
SORRY.

308
00:23:20,566 --> 00:23:23,986
BUT BREAKFAST
IS GONNA HAVE TO WAIT.

309
00:23:25,988 --> 00:23:29,616
I'VE FIGURED OUT A WAY
TO GET US OUT OF HERE.

310
00:23:31,409 --> 00:23:37,250
I GOT A PRETTY GOOD LOOK AT YOUR
COM CONFIGURATION BACK THERE.

311
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:42,420
I THINK I CAN CANNIBALIZE
THE POWER SUPPLY

312
00:23:42,462 --> 00:23:45,966
FROM YOUR TRANSCEIVER...

313
00:23:46,008 --> 00:23:49,345
AND USE IT TO GET MINE WORKING.

314
00:23:49,387 --> 00:23:52,056
MAYBE GET A MESSAGE OFF.

315
00:24:01,399 --> 00:24:03,441
TRIP: GOT IT.

316
00:24:03,483 --> 00:24:05,778
ALMOST THERE.

317
00:24:09,615 --> 00:24:11,992
I THINK THIS IS GOING TO WORK.

318
00:24:12,034 --> 00:24:14,328
ZHO'KAAN: NOHKTO.

319
00:24:14,370 --> 00:24:17,164
TRIP: NO, NOT NOHKTO.

320
00:24:17,206 --> 00:24:19,417
GOOD.

321
00:24:19,457 --> 00:24:20,418
ZHO'KAAN: GOOD.

322
00:24:20,458 --> 00:24:22,460
TRIP: THAT'S RIGHT.

323
00:24:22,502 --> 00:24:24,088
WE'RE GETTING OUT OF HERE.

324
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:25,881
ONCE WE GET BACK TO<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

325
00:24:25,923 --> 00:24:28,175
AND WE CAN FINALLY
UNDERSTAND EACH OTHER,

326
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:31,678
THE FIRST WORDS OUT OF YOUR
MOUTH BETTER BE "THANK YOU."

327
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:34,307
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]
AAH!

328
00:24:34,348 --> 00:24:36,392
[ LAUGHING ]

329
00:24:36,434 --> 00:24:38,727
YOU THINK THAT'S FUNNY?

330
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:46,402
HUH?

331
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:50,488
YOU GONNA LAUGH NOW?

332
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:53,491
TUCKER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

333
00:24:53,533 --> 00:24:57,330
<i>ENTERPRISE,</i> DO YOU READ ME?

334
00:24:57,371 --> 00:24:59,873
COME ON, HOSHI.

335
00:24:59,915 --> 00:25:02,751
TUCKER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

336
00:25:06,088 --> 00:25:08,466
THIS TERRAIN, IT'S ALL VOLCANIC.

337
00:25:08,506 --> 00:25:11,927
IGNEOUS ROCK IS HEAVY
IN DIAMAGNETIC MINERALS.

338
00:25:11,969 --> 00:25:14,512
IT'S INTERFERING
WITH THE TRANSMISSION.

339
00:25:14,554 --> 00:25:16,098
[ SIGHS ]

340
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:20,394
I THINK I KNOW
WHAT WE NEED TO DO.

341
00:25:20,436 --> 00:25:27,485
THE TRANSCEIVER, UM, THE --
THE TSUNSANA...

342
00:25:27,525 --> 00:25:30,070
IT'S BAD DOWN HERE.

343
00:25:30,112 --> 00:25:31,322
NOHKTO.

344
00:25:31,364 --> 00:25:34,200
BUT IF WE TAKE IT
TO HIGHER GROUND,

345
00:25:34,241 --> 00:25:37,619
WE COULD AVOID
SOME OF THE INTERFERENCE.

346
00:25:40,414 --> 00:25:43,042
I'M GONNA NEED HELP.

347
00:25:45,461 --> 00:25:49,631
YOU AND ME, TOGETHER.

348
00:25:59,225 --> 00:26:00,600
SEE?

349
00:26:04,438 --> 00:26:06,023
[ GUN CLATTERS ]

350
00:26:07,774 --> 00:26:10,610
I'M NOT GONNA HURT YOU.

351
00:26:10,652 --> 00:26:15,866
AND YOU...ARE NOT GONNA HURT ME.

352
00:26:19,036 --> 00:26:21,997
WE'LL WORK TOGETHER.

353
00:26:25,459 --> 00:26:27,378
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

354
00:26:44,311 --> 00:26:49,942
BEFORE WE START, WE'LL GET
SOME FOOD FROM YOUR SHIP.

355
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:52,945
YOUR V'DHOZE.

356
00:26:56,532 --> 00:26:57,615
[ GROWLING ]

357
00:26:57,657 --> 00:26:59,118
[ GRUNTING ]

358
00:27:22,266 --> 00:27:23,517
EASY.

359
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:25,685
[ HISSING ]

360
00:27:25,727 --> 00:27:27,480
AAH!

361
00:27:57,843 --> 00:27:59,761
[ GRUNTS ]

362
00:28:05,725 --> 00:28:08,228
[ GRUNTING ]

363
00:28:27,373 --> 00:28:29,749
[ PANTING ]

364
00:28:48,768 --> 00:28:50,729
IS THAT THE BEST YOU CAN DO?

365
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:54,316
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

366
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:19,550
[ GUN CLATTERS ]

367
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:25,514
WE CAN FIGHT SOME MORE
IF YOU WANT.

368
00:29:25,556 --> 00:29:29,393
OR WE CAN TRY
TO GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

369
00:29:29,435 --> 00:29:32,229
[ PANTING ]

370
00:29:32,271 --> 00:29:33,731
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

371
00:29:44,824 --> 00:29:46,660
COME ON.

372
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:01,717
[ BEEPS ]

373
00:30:01,759 --> 00:30:04,219
CAPTAIN, I'M PICKING UP
A TRANSMISSION.

374
00:30:04,261 --> 00:30:05,638
TRIP?

375
00:30:05,679 --> 00:30:08,432
I CAN'T TELL YET.
I'M TRYING TO GET A LOCK.

376
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:17,483
TRIP: CHIEF ENGINEER'S LOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

377
00:30:17,524 --> 00:30:20,694
IT'S BEEN TWO HOURS SINCE WE
STARTED SIGNALING<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

378
00:30:20,736 --> 00:30:22,696
NO RESPONSE YET.

379
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:28,034
THE SUN'S NOT EVEN UP YET, AND
IT'S ALREADY HOTTER THAN HELL.

380
00:30:30,788 --> 00:30:34,291
MY SPARRING PARTNER
DOESN'T LOOK TOO GOOD.

381
00:30:34,333 --> 00:30:40,339
I CAN'T BE SURE, BUT I DON'T
THINK HIS SPECIES CAN SWEAT.

382
00:30:41,799 --> 00:30:47,053
FOR THE RECORD, I HAVE LEARNED
ONE THING ABOUT HIM --

383
00:30:47,095 --> 00:30:50,265
HIS NAME'S ZHO'KAAN.

384
00:30:51,725 --> 00:30:55,813
ANYTHING YOU WANT TO SAY
TO THE FOLKS BACK HOME?

385
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:58,482
ZHO'KAAN: NOHKTO.

386
00:30:58,524 --> 00:31:00,651
TRIP: YEAH.

387
00:31:00,693 --> 00:31:04,070
THAT MEANS "BAD."

388
00:31:04,112 --> 00:31:07,115
YOU WOULD BE PROUD OF ME, HOSHI.

389
00:31:07,157 --> 00:31:12,496
I'VE PICKED UP ABOUT A DOZEN
WORDS IN HIS LANGUAGE.

390
00:31:12,538 --> 00:31:16,625
A COUPLE OF THEM
ARE REAL TONGUE-TWISTERS.

391
00:31:34,727 --> 00:31:36,562
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

392
00:31:59,543 --> 00:32:01,336
HEY.

393
00:32:03,088 --> 00:32:05,090
ZHO'KAAN.

394
00:32:05,131 --> 00:32:07,342
[ SNORTS ]

395
00:32:11,971 --> 00:32:14,015
I THOUGHT I LOST YOU THERE.

396
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:16,894
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

397
00:32:16,935 --> 00:32:20,522
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

398
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:25,068
NO.

399
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:27,738
NO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

400
00:32:30,949 --> 00:32:32,785
ZHO'KAAN: DAMN IT.

401
00:32:49,927 --> 00:32:51,470
DON'T WORRY.

402
00:32:51,511 --> 00:32:53,889
I'LL GET PHLOX TO COOK UP
A NEW BATCH FOR YOU

403
00:32:53,931 --> 00:32:55,515
ONCE WE'RE ABOARD<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

404
00:32:55,557 --> 00:32:57,601
HE'S GREAT WITH
THAT KIND OF THING.

405
00:32:57,643 --> 00:33:00,019
[ GROANING ]

406
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,734
STAY WITH ME, ZHO'KAAN.

407
00:33:05,776 --> 00:33:06,944
[ TRIP SPEAKING
ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

408
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:09,028
DON'T DIE ON ME NOW!

409
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:10,739
UNDERSTAND?

410
00:33:15,786 --> 00:33:17,871
ALL RIGHT.

411
00:33:29,633 --> 00:33:32,761
HOSHI:<i> ENTERPRISE...</i> TUCKER...

412
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:35,138
SEE? I TOLD YOU.

413
00:33:35,180 --> 00:33:37,516
[ STATIC ]

414
00:33:37,557 --> 00:33:39,977
HOSHI, IS THAT YOU?

415
00:33:40,018 --> 00:33:41,812
Trip: Do you read me?
ARCHER: WE READ YOU, TRIP.

416
00:33:41,854 --> 00:33:43,355
Trip: You're just
in time, Captain.

417
00:33:43,396 --> 00:33:45,565
It's starting to get
a little hot down here.

418
00:33:45,607 --> 00:33:47,526
WE'RE GETTING A LOCK
ON YOUR POSITION NOW.

419
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:48,944
Trip: Don't send a shuttlepod.

420
00:33:48,986 --> 00:33:51,154
THERE'S SOMETHING
IN THIS ATMOSPHERE

421
00:33:51,196 --> 00:33:52,572
THAT'LL AFFECT THE ENGINES.

422
00:33:52,614 --> 00:33:54,574
Archer: It's selenium isotopes.

423
00:33:54,616 --> 00:33:57,870
But we don't think it will
interfere with the transporter.

424
00:33:57,911 --> 00:33:59,412
I'M NOT ALONE, CAPTAIN.

425
00:33:59,454 --> 00:34:02,332
Archer: We know. The Arkonians
helped us find you.

426
00:34:02,374 --> 00:34:05,335
How are you and their pilot
getting along?

427
00:34:05,377 --> 00:34:09,006
UH, JUST LIKE OLD FRIENDS.

428
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:12,009
I'M A LITTLE WORRIED, THOUGH.

429
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:14,052
HE'S GOTTEN VERY DEHYDRATED.

430
00:34:14,093 --> 00:34:15,136
STAND BY, TRIP.

431
00:34:15,178 --> 00:34:16,680
PREPARE THE TRANSPORTER.

432
00:34:16,722 --> 00:34:19,016
I WOULDN'T DO THAT, CAPTAIN.

433
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:20,767
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

434
00:34:20,809 --> 00:34:23,395
PHLOX: I'VE BEEN ANALYZING
THE ARKONIANS' PHYSIOLOGY.

435
00:34:23,436 --> 00:34:26,105
THEIR ENDOCRINE SYSTEM
IS EXTREMELY SENSITIVE

436
00:34:26,147 --> 00:34:27,691
TO TEMPERATURE FLUCTUATIONS.

437
00:34:27,733 --> 00:34:29,985
IF THAT PILOT IS SUFFERING
FROM DEHYDRATION,

438
00:34:30,027 --> 00:34:32,905
IT'S NO DOUBT CAUSING
AN ACUTE CELLULAR BREAKDOWN.

439
00:34:32,946 --> 00:34:34,155
MEANING?

440
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:37,993
TRANSPORTING HIM
WILL MOST LIKELY BE FATAL.

441
00:34:39,953 --> 00:34:42,998
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
Archer: Archer
to Commander Tucker.

442
00:34:43,040 --> 00:34:44,624
I'M STILL HERE, CAPTAIN.

443
00:34:44,666 --> 00:34:46,668
Archer: Trip, we can
bring you aboard,

444
00:34:46,710 --> 00:34:49,295
but we can't transport
the Arkonian.

445
00:34:49,337 --> 00:34:51,089
Dr. Phlox says it will kill him.

446
00:34:51,130 --> 00:34:53,717
We'll try to find a way
to get him back to his ship.

447
00:34:53,759 --> 00:34:57,345
BUT IN THE MEANTIME,
I'M GETTING YOU OUT OF THERE.

448
00:34:57,387 --> 00:34:58,555
Trip: No way, Captain.

449
00:34:58,597 --> 00:35:00,265
I'm not leaving him here.

450
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:02,935
THE SURFACE TEMPERATURE
IS RISING QUICKLY, COMMANDER.

451
00:35:02,976 --> 00:35:06,646
I ESTIMATE IT WILL REACH 130
DEGREES WITHIN THE NEXT HOUR.

452
00:35:06,688 --> 00:35:08,189
LET'S GET YOU HOME.

453
00:35:08,231 --> 00:35:09,942
Archer: Then we'll worry
about your friend.

454
00:35:09,983 --> 00:35:12,193
I'M SORRY, SIR,
BUT I CAN'T DO THAT.

455
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:14,613
Trip: Maybe there's another way.

456
00:35:14,654 --> 00:35:19,242
WE KNOW OUR PODS
CAN'T MAKE IT...

457
00:35:19,284 --> 00:35:21,494
BUT I GOT A GOOD LOOK
AT THE CIRCUITRY

458
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:24,581
INSIDE THE ARKONIAN SHUTTLE.

459
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:27,000
ONE OF THEIRS COULD BE MODIFIED.

460
00:35:27,042 --> 00:35:28,501
HOW?

461
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:30,587
Trip: If they take a look
at their intake manifolds,

462
00:35:30,629 --> 00:35:35,675
I THINK THEY COULD REALIGN THEM
TO FILTER OUT THE ISOTOPES.

463
00:35:35,717 --> 00:35:37,761
WE'LL TALK TO THEM,

464
00:35:37,803 --> 00:35:40,889
BUT I WON'T LET YOU
STAY DOWN THERE MUCH LONGER.

465
00:35:40,931 --> 00:35:43,976
UNDERSTOOD.

466
00:35:44,017 --> 00:35:45,727
Archer: Archer out.

467
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:58,865
TUCKER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

468
00:36:00,742 --> 00:36:05,163
<i>ENTERPRISE,</i> RESPOND.

469
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:11,003
SOME OF THESE RELAYS HAVE FUSED.

470
00:36:11,044 --> 00:36:13,379
[ SIGHS ]

471
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:16,049
MUST BE THE HEAT.

472
00:36:20,095 --> 00:36:21,763
HEY.

473
00:36:23,807 --> 00:36:26,059
[ TRIP SPEAKING
ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

474
00:36:28,227 --> 00:36:30,396
[ GROANING ]

475
00:36:42,993 --> 00:36:46,579
I DON'T SUPPOSE
THE CAPTAIN'LL TRUST ME

476
00:36:46,621 --> 00:36:49,248
TO GO OUT ON MY OWN FOR A WHILE.

477
00:36:49,290 --> 00:36:54,046
I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED IF
HE KNOCKED ME DOWN TO STEWARD.

478
00:36:55,672 --> 00:36:58,216
"YOUR ORANGE JUICE, SIR.

479
00:36:58,257 --> 00:37:00,802
JAM OR MARMALADE, SIR?"

480
00:37:00,844 --> 00:37:07,225
BUT I TELL YOU, I WOULDN'T TRADE
MY TIME ON<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

481
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:09,811
NOT FOR ANYTHING.

482
00:37:11,312 --> 00:37:15,316
I'VE SEEN THINGS I COULDN'T
HAVE IMAGINED BACK HOME.

483
00:37:15,358 --> 00:37:20,530
I SAW THE GREAT PLUME
OF AGOSORIA,

484
00:37:20,572 --> 00:37:26,661
AND I SAW THE RINGED MOONS
OF MATALAS PRIME.

485
00:37:36,671 --> 00:37:41,176
AND I STOOD
ON AN ASTEROID CRATER...

486
00:37:42,301 --> 00:37:44,470
...TWICE AS HIGH AS EVEREST

487
00:37:44,512 --> 00:37:48,307
AND WENT DIVING
IN THE ICE CAVES OF ETHEENIA.

488
00:37:48,349 --> 00:37:53,438
RODE IN A SULIBAN CELL SHIP.

489
00:37:53,479 --> 00:37:55,232
SPENT THE NIGHT...

490
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:58,610
I SPENT THE NIGHT
WITH A PRINCESS.

491
00:37:58,651 --> 00:38:01,196
[ CHUCKLES ]

492
00:38:01,238 --> 00:38:03,281
OH, AND I...

493
00:38:03,322 --> 00:38:06,492
I EVEN GOT PREGNANT ONCE.

494
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:09,955
NOW, THERE'S A STORY.

495
00:38:11,664 --> 00:38:14,375
I'M SURE YOU HAVE STORIES, TOO.

496
00:38:14,417 --> 00:38:17,462
THAT'S WHY WE CHOSE
THIS LIFE, RIGHT?

497
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:20,423
SEE THINGS WE'VE
NEVER SEEN BEFORE.

498
00:38:20,465 --> 00:38:24,636
HELL OF A RIDE, THOUGH.

499
00:38:27,555 --> 00:38:30,600
HELL OF A RIDE.

500
00:38:39,109 --> 00:38:41,194
ZHO'KAAN.

501
00:38:41,236 --> 00:38:43,488
[ COUGHING ]

502
00:38:43,529 --> 00:38:46,199
V'DHOZE.

503
00:39:04,134 --> 00:39:05,177
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

504
00:39:05,218 --> 00:39:06,344
COME IN.

505
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:13,434
I JUST GOT A REPORT
FROM MY DOCTOR.

506
00:39:13,476 --> 00:39:16,021
YOUR PILOT'S RESPONDING WELL.

507
00:39:16,062 --> 00:39:19,398
HE'LL BE READY TO GO HOME
IN A FEW HOURS.

508
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:21,067
AND YOUR CREWMAN?

509
00:39:21,109 --> 00:39:26,447
HE'S TIRED AND A BIT SUNBURNED,
BUT HE'S DOING FINE.

510
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:29,201
IF I DISCOVER THAT MY PILOT

511
00:39:29,242 --> 00:39:32,912
FIRED ON YOUR SHUTTLE
WITHOUT PROVOCATION,

512
00:39:32,954 --> 00:39:34,664
HE'LL BE DISCIPLINED.

513
00:39:34,706 --> 00:39:38,793
IT WAS A MISUNDERSTANDING.

514
00:39:38,835 --> 00:39:42,588
I HOPE WE CAN AVOID THEM
IN THE FUTURE.

515
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:47,802
I EXPECT YOU TO LEAVE THIS
SYSTEM IMMEDIATELY, AS AGREED.

516
00:39:59,856 --> 00:40:02,275
I GUESS WE WON'T BE ADDING
THE ARKONIANS

517
00:40:02,317 --> 00:40:03,860
TO OUR LIST OF FRIENDS.

518
00:40:03,902 --> 00:40:06,654
THE ENCOUNTER WAS LESS VOLATILE
THAN I EXPECTED.

519
00:40:06,696 --> 00:40:08,865
[ CHUCKLES ]

520
00:40:08,907 --> 00:40:11,868
YOU MANAGED TO ESTABLISH
BETTER RELATIONS

521
00:40:11,910 --> 00:40:16,206
IN A SINGLE DAY THAN THE VULCANS
HAVE IN A CENTURY.

522
00:40:18,875 --> 00:40:21,753
LET'S HOPE IT STAYS THAT WAY.

523
00:40:27,300 --> 00:40:28,968
HOW'S HE DOING?

524
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:31,221
WHY DON'T YOU ASK HIM YOURSELF?

525
00:40:31,263 --> 00:40:34,266
THE UNIVERSAL TRANSLATOR
IS ONLINE.

526
00:40:37,685 --> 00:40:41,731
THEY, UH, TOLD ME ANOTHER
10 MINUTES OF SUNSHINE,

527
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:45,235
AND WE'D HAVE BEEN COOKED.

528
00:40:45,277 --> 00:40:48,154
TARRATT-AASH.

529
00:40:48,196 --> 00:40:50,865
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
THE U.T. WAS WORKING.

530
00:40:50,907 --> 00:40:56,955
I BELIEVE YOU PROMISED ME
SOME TARRATT-AASH.

531
00:40:56,996 --> 00:40:59,999
YOU MEAN THE BROWN STUFF
YOU WERE DRINKING.

532
00:41:01,334 --> 00:41:03,211
TRIP: WON'T TAKE A MINUTE.

533
00:41:03,253 --> 00:41:05,380
ANYTHING ELSE WHILE I'M AT IT?

534
00:41:05,422 --> 00:41:10,260
OUR CHEF IS MAKING SOMETHING
CALLED CHICKEN MARSALA TONIGHT.

535
00:41:10,302 --> 00:41:12,595
TARRATT...

536
00:41:12,637 --> 00:41:15,223
TRIP: TARRATT-AASH.

537
00:41:15,265 --> 00:41:17,309
GOTCHA.

538
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:20,561
TRIP.

539
00:41:20,603 --> 00:41:23,815
WHEN I FIRED AT YOUR VESSEL...

540
00:41:27,944 --> 00:41:31,281
I'M GRATEFUL
I DIDN'T DESTROY IT.

541
00:41:33,532 --> 00:41:35,785
THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

542
00:41:43,542 --> 00:41:45,462
[ DOOR OPENS ]
